Attributes -  extra information about tags

Types of attributes:
1. Global Attributes - can be used with any tag. Examples: id, class, tabIndex, draggable*, dropzone*, hidden, title
- id: uniquely identifies an element
- class: grouping certain elements
- tabIndex: defines the order in which elements receive focus when navigating with the Tab key
- draggable: specifies whether an element can be dragged. Set to true, it makes the element draggable; set to false, it disables  dragging. By default, images and links are draggable. This attribute supports both native drag-and-drop behavior and custom interactions via JavaScript.
- hidden: hides an element on the webpage (present in DOM)

2. Core Attributes - important attributes. Example: id, class, style

3. Internalization Attributes - adapt web document for different language and alignment. dir(ltr, rtl, auto), lang 
- lang: specifies the language
- dir: alignment (ltr/rtl)

4. Element Specific Attributes - belong to a certain tag. Examples: src, href, type, action, placeholder
5. Custom Attributes - user-defined attributes. Can be defined using JavaScript. Syntax: data-myAttributeName

* can be used through javascript

Lists:
1. Ordered List: tags: <ol>, <li> ; type: 1(default), A, a, I, i
2. Unordered List: <ul>, <li> ; type: disc(default), circle, sqaure, none
3. Description List: <dl>, <dt>, <dd>
4. Nested Lists: list within a list. Add <ol>/<ul> inside <li>

Tables: structured representation of data
- Tags for Table:
1. <table> </table> : Attributes: rules, cellspacing (space between the cells), cellpadding(space between the text in the cell,  and cell border), border, height, width
2. <tr> </tr>
3. <th> </th> : the text is center aligned and bold
4. <td> </td> : Attributes: colspan, rowspan

- Attributes for Table:
1. border : introducing table border
2. colspan : merging columns ; valued (td)
3. rowspan : merging rows (td)

